{"title": "Modern Utopia", "description": "H. G. Wells's proposal for social reform was the formation of a world state, a concept that would increasingly preoccupy him throughout the remainder of his life. One of his most ambitious early attempts at portraying a world state was <i>A Modern Utopia</i> (1905). <i>A Modern Utopia</i> was intended as a hybrid between fiction and 'philosophical discussion'. Like most utopists, he has indicated a series of modifications which in his opinion would increase the aggregate of human happiness. Basically, Wells' idea of a perfect world would be if everyone were able to live a happy life. This book is written with an intimate knowledge of former ideal commonwealths and is a conscious attempt to describe a utopia that is not utopian. (Summary by Wikipedia)", "duration": 36661, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "146", "name": "H. G. Wells"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt22/modern_utopia_1210.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["General Fiction", "*Non-fiction", "Political Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Alisson Veldhuis"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Carl Manchester"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Bill Boerst"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction: The Owner of the Voice", "readers": [4712], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/modernutopia_1207_librivox/amodernutopia_00_wells_64kb.mp3", "duration": 728}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1: Topographical", "readers": [4712], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/modernutopia_1207_librivox/amodernutopia_01_wells_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2501}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2: Concerning Freedoms, Sections 1-3", "readers": [6294], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/modernutopia_1207_librivox/amodernutopia_02_wells_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1875}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 2: Concerning Freedoms, Secti